<tr>
<td><span>$[x]^j$</span></td>
<td>1</td>
<td><span>$x$</span></td>
<td><span>$x^2$</span></td>
<td><span>$x+1$</span></td>
<td><span>$x^2+x$</span></td>
<td><span>$x^2+x+1$</span></td>
<td><span>$x^2+1$</span></td>
<td>1</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>The inverse is <span>$[x]^6$</span> (for <span>$[x] \cdot [x]^6 = 1$</span>.</p>
<h3 class="header"><i>5.1</i>Accuracy and discussion<a class="headerlink" href="#accuracy-and-discussion_4" name="accuracy-and-discussion_4">&para;</a></h3>
